gm-method: when auditing doc-vs-code completeness, the highest-yield witness is grepping the live constant/enum in source against the documented value. A doc enumerating N items where the code constant has M>N is a stale-doc discovery -> prd-add a fix row this turn, never narrate it as 'minor'. Concrete trap pattern: a doc 'canonical set' list plus a 'default = X' claim both drift independently from the code's actual array constant and its default-resolution branch; verify BOTH the membership list and the default-when-empty branch by reading the function, not just the constant. Multiple divergent copies of the same-named constant across modules (3 FALLBACK_ON definitions with different lengths) is itself a finding worth a reconcile row.